 {"id":"brenner_bot-ei6","title":"Task: Verify 60fps animations on mobile","description":"Ensure all animations run at 60fps on mobile devices.

## Purpose

Janky animations destroy the feeling of quality. 60fps animations feel 'native'.

## Current Animations to Verify

- Page transitions (fade-in-up)
- Card hover states (desktop) / tap states (mobile)
- Bottom sheet open/close
- Search modal open/close
- Reading progress bar
- Back-to-top button appearance

## Testing Method

1. Open Chrome DevTools
2. Performance panel → Frame rate
3. Trigger each animation
4. Verify frames maintain 60fps
5. On actual mobile device if possible

## Common Performance Issues

### Layout Thrashing
- Animating width/height causes reflow
- Use transform instead

### Paint Storms
- Animating colors on large areas
- Use opacity and transform instead

### Compositor Misses
- Not using will-change or translateZ
- Add hints for animated elements

## Optimizations If Needed

```css
.animated-element {
  will-change: transform, opacity;
  transform: translateZ(0); /* Force GPU layer */
}
```

### React Performance
- Memoize animated components
- Avoid re-renders during animation
- Use CSS transitions not JS

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All animations tested in DevTools
- [ ] 60fps maintained for each animation
- [ ] Tested on actual mobile device
- [ ] No jank during scroll
- [ ] No jank during page transitions
